<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=576&amp;p=4669#p4669"><![CDATA[
Alright, I registered so I can edit my posts...<br /><br />The kevtris quote should actually read:<br /><br />"PPU access: You have A0-A13, /A13, D0-D7, /WR and /RD. /A13 is usually connected to /CE of the CIRAM to enable it for addresses 2000-3FFF. <br />Likewise, A13 is usually used to enable the C-ROM or C-RAM on the cart <br />(which is then mapped into 0000-1FFF). " <br /><br />I redid the famicom schematic changing the pinouts to the NES pinouts and labling each pin. Get it <a href="http://img70.imageshack.us/img70/7050/ntd8bitnes4qk.jpg" class="postlink">here</a> if you want : <br /><br />Using the info given in the schematic it appears that (Mario Bros 2 does short pin 57 and 58 together, but) pin 58 is actually /A13. I tested this with a multimeter (on continuity) and it seems this is correct. easier to show the rest of what I want to say in an image:<br /><br /><img src="http://img195.imageshack.us/img195/5866/snip8uw.jpg" alt="Image" /><br /><br />Thanks, maybe this will help someone in the future!!<br /><br />[edit]<br />Addional info: <br /><br />The 74373 doesn't seem to be connected in a logical fashion on the NES, don't go by the shematic. It's not worth figuring out though. [EDIT] Changed my mind. The edited schematic now accurately shows the connections to the 373 on the NES.<br /><br />The famicom sound lines on the cart connector I left blank. They supposedly go to the EXP connector or something on the NES, but I don't care.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=196">Movax</a> — Sun Sep 18, 2005 4:07 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
