I'm confused:<br /><br />PPU memory<br /> $0000   to $1FFF is Chr RAM/ROM ie pattern tables, right?<br /><br />I notice my Super Mario Bros 2 cart shorts pin 57 (CIRAM /CE) and 58 (CHR A13) effective doing what Kevtris says in his Nes Cart types doc:<br /><br />"PPU access:  You have A0-A13, /A13, D0-D7, /WR and /RD.  A13 is usually connected to /CE of the CIRAM to enable it for addresses 0000-1FFF.  <br />Likewise, /A13 is usually used to enable the C-ROM or C-RAM on the cart<br />(which is then mapped into 2000-3FFF).  "<br /><br />But then isn't this the opposite of the given (in all nes docs) PPU memory map? Or do only plane jane 32K/8K or less carts have their pattern tables at $0000 to $1FFF ?<p>Statistics: Posted by Guest — Sun Sep 18, 2005 3:12 am</p><hr />
